<div id="Idea_4107"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaTitle">
<a href="/akira/dtd/4107-4049"><span id="IdeaTitle_4107">Building the Future We Need&nbsp;</span></a>
</div>
<table width=@%">  <tr>    <td valign="top"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaSubTitle"><b><a href="http://opengov.ideascale.com/akira/pmd/9728-4049">drsolarrob2</a></b> <span class="IdeaScale_SecondaryText">1 day ago</span></div></td>    <td align="right" valign="top"></td>  </tr></table>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaContent">If we are to Resolve the Energy and Climate Issues, in a time period soon enough, to matter to the most people, we have to begin the Community Planning Processes required, NOW, ... So All can come to understand what ( we ) should be doing.<br/><br/>The President and his Cabinet have to be fully involved in this Rebuild America Planning process, and the Congress must be ready to Legislate any required changes or additions to existing Federal Law. States must be involved too.<br/><br/>Each Cabinet Secretary, and the Agencies they are responsible for must be fully vested in the process too.<br/><br/>To Rebuild America, of course, requires that the People should be involved too, but basic planning must proceed their full involvement. The point being, that we do not want a hodge podge of wildly different Plans, but a general Plan that can be ( locally ) modified as needed.<br/><br/>To those reading this DIALOG, ... Please understand, this is a very involved process, and cannot be fully expressed here.<br/><br/>FOR ALL ... Suffice to say, our current Homes and Businesses, our Transportation Systems, and our Food supply systems, will become IMPOSSIBLE to maintain, on our present path.  ( Using what some call technology fixes, must be looked at more seriously, since Energy and Resources will be in short supply.)<br/><br/>The Planning must result in a United States of America, that will be here in 3009.  Our thinking on a Quarterly, three month timescale, is no way of Planning.<br/><br/>The President must return a REPLY, if he is serious about addressing the Energy and Climate Issues.  We must begin NOW ! </div>
