<td valign="top" style="padding-right:30px; padding-left:20px;">
<div id="Idea_4024"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaTitle">
<a href="/akira/dtd/4024-4049"><span id="IdeaTitle_4024">Increased Access to Healthcare&nbsp;</span></a>
</div>
<table width=@%">  <tr>    <td valign="top"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaSubTitle"><b><a href="http://opengov.ideascale.com/akira/pmd/9175-4049">sanjiv733</a></b> <span class="IdeaScale_SecondaryText">2 days ago</span></div></td>    <td align="right" valign="top"></td>  </tr></table>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaContent">There is currently a shortage of sub-specialist physicians in America.  As a result, most U.S. sub-specialists earn significantly higher salaries than their counterparts in other developed countries.  This supply-demand disparity can be corrected by reducing the barriers to entry for sub-specialists from other English speaking countries.  For example, instead of requiring these physicians to repeat their multi-year residencies and sometimes fellowships, the U.S. medical system could simply require an abbreviated 1 year residency that is more aimed at acclimating these physicians to the U.S. system rather than focusing on "re-educaiton." </div>
