</div>
<table width=@%">  <tr>    <td valign="top"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaSubTitle"><b><a href="http://opengov.ideascale.com/akira/pmd/8541-4049">packolman</a></b> <span class="IdeaScale_SecondaryText">2 days ago</span></div></td>    <td align="right" valign="top"></td>  </tr></table>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaContent">an idea would be to use fiat issues on potential value gained through infrastructure and industrial contruction as well as contruction of lowcost public housing. This would allow the president to jump start the production and consumption base of the economy by building both demand and consumption. As well as having a supplus value through controling contruction that could be used to negate existing treasury bonds. Projects should be geared to a value added of 4 to 1. Meaning 4 dollars of value would be added for every one created. Then you levy the remaining 3 against the debt by privitsing the idustrial parts. The one you started with would then be left to secure the money supply. An additional fiat issue may be needed to created more assets of value whose titles would remain in the treasury in order to increase the value of dollar and/or serve as reserve credit source. </div>
